title: 103_hr1288
content: There is no information provided in the prev_chunk to assist with summarizing the curr_chunk. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States is amended by changing the date from "12/31/92" to "12/31/94" for various headings, including chemicals like p-Toluenesulfonyl chloride, 2,6-Dichlorobenzaldehyde, and others. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States is amended to update the date to "12/31/94" for various chemicals, including naphthalenesulfonic acid, 3,3'-Dimethoxybenzidine, 2-Amino-5-nitrophenol, 1-Amino-2,4-dibromoanthraquinone, and others. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States is amended to update the date for various chemicals, including methylphenylpyrazolone, 3-Methyl-5-pyrazolone, 2-Amino-N-ethylbenzenesulfonoanilide, and other chemical compounds. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States is amended to update the date for various chemicals, including different compounds like 4-Amino-1-naphthalenesulfonic acid, 8-Amino-2-naphthalenesulfonic acid, mixtures of 5- and 8-amino-2-naphthalenesulfonic acid, 1-Naphthylamine, 6-Amino-2-naphthalenesulfonic acid, 2,4-Diaminobenzenesulfonic acid, 2-Amino-4-chlorophenol, 1-Amino-2-methoxybenzene, and 7-Anilino-4-hydroxy-2-naphthalenesulfonic acid. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States is amended to update the date for various chemicals, including compounds like naphthalenesulfonic acid, 1,4-Diamino-2,3-dihydroanthraquinone, 1-Amino-2-bromo-4-hydroxyanthraquinone, 4-Aminoacetanilide, 2-[(4-Aminophenyl)sulfonyl]ethanol, 2,5-Dichloro-4-(3-methyl-5-oxo-2-pyrazolin-1-yl)-benzenesulfonic acid, 1,3,3-Trimethyl-2-methyleneindoline, and 7-Nitronaphth[1,2]-oxadiazole-5-sulphonic acid. The amendments made by section 1 of this Act will take effect 15 days after enactment. A retroactive provision allows for lower duty on goods entered or withdrawn from warehouse between December 31, 1992, and the 15th day after enactment to be liquidated or reliquidated upon request before the 90th day after enactment.
